      "content": "that makes sense. when you say \"demographic shifts\" and \"turnover\" create more risk, are you implying that certain types of new residents—specifically from different ethnic or cultural backgrounds—tend to be less stable for property values? just trying to understand if the risk is purely about the frequency of moving or if it's about the actual makeup of the population changing.",
